@page "/trip"
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Trip";
}

<section class="journey-hero">
  <div class="journey-intro">
    <div class="badge">Trip</div>
    <h1>Itinerary notes, scenic stops, and a page with a calmer rhythm.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A dedicated travel page for plans, stops along the way, and short notes that do not need to live on the homepage.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="journey-panel">
    <div class="journey-label">Current route idea</div>
    <strong>Prague → Alps → Lakeside return</strong>
    <p class="muted">A mix of road trip planning, calm stops, and a simple checklist.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="trip-layout">
    <article class="trip-stop">
      <div class="card-kicker">Stop 01</div>
      <h2>Departure Window</h2>
      <p>Plan the departure outside rush hour and keep the first part of the trip as stress-free as possible.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="trip-stop">
      <div class="card-kicker">Stop 02</div>
      <h2>Scenic Break</h2>
      <p>A stop for the view, coffee, and a short walk. This page is shaped more like an editorial page than a dashboard.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="trip-stop">
      <div class="card-kicker">Stop 03</div>
      <h2>Evening Landing</h2>
      <p>Arrive with enough buffer so the end of the day is not just logistics. Space for notes or a gallery can be added later.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
